  "tune": "God Rest Ye Merry Gentlemen",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "God rest ye merry, gentlemen, let nothing you dismay, Remember Christ our Savior was born on Christmas Day; To save us all from Satan&#39;s pow&#39;r when we were gone astray. O tidings of comfort and joy, comfort and joy; O tidings of comfort and joy.",
    "v2": "In Bethlehem, in Israel, this blessèd Babe was born, And laid within a manger upon this blessèd morn; The which His mother Mary did nothing take in scorn. O tidings of comfort and joy, comfort and joy; O tidings of comfort and joy.",
    "v3": "From God our heav&#39;nly Father a blessèd angel came; And unto certain shepherds brought tidings of the same; How that in Bethlehem was born the Son of God by name. O tidings of comfort and joy, comfort and joy; O tidings of comfort and joy.",
    "v4": "&quot;Fear not, then,&quot; said the angel, &quot;Let nothing you afright This day is born a Savior of a pure Virgin bright, To free all those who trust in Him from Satan&#39;s pow&#39;r and might.&quot; O tidings of comfort and joy, comfort and joy; O tidings of comfort and joy.",
    "v5": "The shepherds at those tidings rejoiced much in mind, And left their flocks afeeding in tempest, storm and wind, And went to Bethl&#39;em straightaway this blessèd Babe to find. O tidings of comfort and joy, comfort and joy; O tidings of comfort and joy."
  },
